Given Data:
- Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -1,028,375.55
- Net Profit (Net Income) = 835,266.51

The Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio is calculated as:

\[
\text{Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio} = \frac{\text{Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities}}{\text{Net Income}}
\]

Substitute values:

\[
= \frac{-1,028,375.55}{835,266.51} \approx -1.231
\]

Rounding to two decimal places: -1.23

So the Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio is approximately -1.23.

